The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, July 24: India has prepared a liberal offering in services, including telecom, financial and courier sectors. This will be discussed by the cabinet committee on WTO tomorrow. The revised services offer entails committing existing liberalisation in various sectors at the WTO. However, the proposal will not have any offer on opening of the retail sector. This comes at a time when multi-lateral trade talks in Geneva are gathering pace.

 New Delhi, July 24: Prime Minister Manmohan Singh has cleared the Oil and Natural Gas Corporations Rs 21,000 crore investment in LNG, power and petrochemicals projects at Mangalore. ONGC?s projects include a Rs 7,475-crore petrochemicals and aromatic plant and a Rs 8594-crore LNG-based power project.

 New Delhi, July 24: The cabinet is expected to give its clearance to a Rs 1,700-crore project to set up three auto test and research facilities at its next meeting.

 New Delhi, July 24: The Germany-based Continental is looking at setting up a dedicated captive facility in India, a company official has said. The 15-billion-euro company has an annual spend of about $300 million for sourcing various IT-related requirements.

 New Delhi, July 24: The finance ministry has asked all PSU banks to submit by Monday a ?statement of intent?, which would lay down the financial targets for 2005-06.




